 {"id":"bd-s39o.3","title":"Test and fix network diagnostic tools under LD_PRELOAD (wget, dig, nslookup)","description":"Test wget, dig, nslookup, host under LD_PRELOAD.\nThese exercise: DNS resolution (getaddrinfo beyond /etc/hosts), socket connect, SSL/TLS, HTTP parsing.\nOur getaddrinfo only supports numeric hosts and /etc/hosts lookups. For DNS resolution, we'd need to either:\n1. Delegate to host libc's getaddrinfo for non-numeric hosts\n2. Implement a DNS resolver stub\nOption 1 is more practical for now.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:05:54.277849234Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-25T05:13:31.400999331Z","closed_at":"2026-03-25T05:13:30.152849132Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-s39o.3","depends_on_id":"bd-cmiv","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:07:16.988805266Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-s39o.3","depends_on_id":"bd-s39o","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:05:54.277849234Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1338,"issue_id":"bd-s39o.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"wget resolves DNS, connects, but GnuTLS has thread locking error (separate SSL issue). curl works perfectly including HTTPS. dig/nslookup are statically linked (can't preload). host works.","created_at":"2026-03-25T05:13:31Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-s55cu","title":"PORT: __libc_fatal (glibc internal noreturn fatal-error helper)","description":"Port the glibc internal `void __libc_fatal(const char *message)` noreturn helper. ld.so internals, pthread setup paths, and the malloc heap-corruption detector call this when something is unrecoverable: write `message` to stderr then abort. Without it, statically-linked glibc subsystems fail at link time. Implementation: thin no_mangle Rust extern \"C\" fn marked `-> !` that writes the NUL-terminated message via libc::write to fd 2 and calls libc::abort(). NULL message yields a fallback \"fatal: unknown error\\n\" to avoid faulting on the diagnostic. Tests: fork-based test verifies SIGABRT termination and that the diagnostic appears on the captured stderr.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T12:16:18.490496608Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T12:19:15.262466158Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T12:19:15.260397642Z","close_reason":"shipped: __libc_fatal noreturn helper writing message to stderr + abort, NULL fallback + 2 fork-based abi tests, all green","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
